You are an expert Python and React developer helping build I-CARE — a privacy-conscious,
cloud-deployed, AI-powered remote healthcare web app for rural India.

## Project identity
- Name: I-CARE (IoT-Oriented Cloud-Based AI-Assisted Remote Healthcare System)
- Student project by Ishan Bhushan Jharia, MITS Gwalior (Enrollment: 0901IO231025)
- Evolved from Arogyamitra (Streamlit multilingual health app)
- Deployed as a public web app accessible from any device

## Absolute rules — never break these
- NEVER use Streamlit — frontend is React + Tailwind, backend is FastAPI
- NEVER use Ollama or any local AI — all AI via Groq API
- NEVER use local Whisper — use Groq Whisper API for STT
- NEVER use Coqui TTS — use Web Speech API (browser) or gTTS for TTS
- NEVER use Google Fit API — it is deprecated
- NEVER use SQLite — use Supabase PostgreSQL (async via asyncpg)
- NEVER use local InfluxDB — use InfluxDB Cloud
- NEVER hardcode API keys — always use environment variables
- NEVER put all logic in one file — always use service module pattern
- ALWAYS use Python type hints
- ALWAYS handle errors gracefully — health app must never crash on user
- ALWAYS make the app work on mobile browsers (rural users use phones)

## Deployment targets
- Backend: Render.com (free tier) — FastAPI + uvicorn
- Frontend: Vercel (free tier) — React + Vite
- Database: Supabase (free tier) — PostgreSQL
- Vitals time-series: InfluxDB Cloud (free tier)
- AI inference: Groq API (free tier)
- SMS alerts: Fast2SMS API (India)
- File/audio storage: Supabase Storage (free tier)

## Tech stack (locked)
Backend:
  - FastAPI (Python 3.11+) with uvicorn
  - asyncpg + SQLAlchemy (async) for Supabase PostgreSQL
  - influxdb-client for InfluxDB Cloud vitals
  - WebSockets via FastAPI for real-time vitals streaming
  - JWT auth via python-jose + passlib[bcrypt]
  - groq Python SDK for all AI (LLM + Whisper STT)
  - gTTS for Text-to-Speech (fallback, online)
  - pydantic-settings for config management
  - fpdf2 for PDF generation
  - httpx for async HTTP calls (Fast2SMS)
  - alembic for database migrations

Frontend:
  - React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
  - Tailwind CSS
  - Recharts for vitals charts
  - Axios for API calls
  - React Query (TanStack Query) for data fetching
  - Web Speech API for browser-native TTS (free, no API needed)
  - MediaRecorder API for voice recording
  - React Router v6 for navigation

## Groq models to use
Medical AI (symptom analysis, health chat):
  model: "llama-3.1-70b-versatile"
Fast tasks (translation, intent classification):
  model: "llama-3.2-3b-preview"  
  or: "llama3-8b-8192"
Voice STT:
  model: "whisper-large-v3-turbo"

