## Vitals thresholds
heart_rate: warn_high=100, alert_high=130, critical_high=180, warn_low=50, critical_low=40
spo2: alert_low=94, critical_low=88
bp_systolic: warn_high=140, critical_high=180, warn_low=90, critical_low=80
bp_diastolic: warn_high=90, critical_high=120, warn_low=60, critical_low=50

## Alert escalation
Level 1: In-app notification — immediate
Level 2: In-app red alert — unacknowledged 60s
Level 3: Fast2SMS to patient — unacknowledged 120s
Level 4: Fast2SMS to caregiver — unacknowledged 180s
Level 5: SMS all contacts + show emergency button — critical vitals

## Languages supported
Hindi, English, Marathi, Tamil, Telugu, Bengali, Gujarati, Kannada, Malayalam, Punjabi

## Mobile-first design rules
- All pages must work on 375px width (phone screen)
- Touch targets minimum 44px height
- No hover-only interactions
- Bottom navigation bar on mobile
- Sidebar collapses to hamburger on mobile
- Voice button always visible and large enough to tap

## Render deployment specifics
- Add backend/Procfile: web: uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT
- Add backend/runtime.txt: python-3.11.0
- CORS must allow Vercel frontend URL + localhost for dev
- WebSockets must work on Render free tier (they do)
- Wake-up ping endpoint GET /health must respond in <100ms

## Supabase specifics
- Use async SQLAlchemy with asyncpg driver
- Connection string format: postgresql+asyncpg://user:pass@host/db
- Use connection pooling: pool_size=5, max_overflow=10
- Run alembic migrations before deployment

## InfluxDB Cloud specifics
- Use influxdb-client-python with async client
- Measurement: patient_vitals
- Tags: patient_id, metric, source
- Fields: value (float), unit (string)
- Always use try/except — if InfluxDB fails, app continues (non-critical)
